---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
	title="About"
	description="About Ethan Pham, and the mix of Project Euler, competitive programming, essays, and code notes on this site."
>
	<section class="page-intro">
		<span class="eyebrow">About</span>
		<h1>I use this site to keep my work and study notes in one place.</h1>
		<p>
			I'm Ethan Pham, also known as Pham Van Nghia on GitHub. This site is where I keep the things I
			want to revisit later: Project Euler write-ups, competitive programming solutions, essays, and
			small technical notes. The subjects I keep circling back to are AI/ML, algorithms, algebra, and
			post-quantum cryptography.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section class="section-panel">
		<div class="track-grid">
			<div class="card" data-tone="warm">
				<h3>What is on the site</h3>
				<p>
					It started with Project Euler and grew from there. Now it also includes a competitive
					programming section for ICPC and IOI, along with essays and short code notes.
				</p>
			</div>
			<div class="card" data-tone="cool">
				<h3>What I am interested in</h3>
				<p>
					Right now that mostly means AI/ML, algorithmic problem solving, algebra, number theory,
					and lattice-based post-quantum cryptography. I am usually happiest when the implementation
					work and the underlying reasoning both matter.
				</p>
			</div>
			<div class="card" data-tone="olive">
				<h3>How I like to work</h3>
				<p>
					I like keeping the explanation close to the code, especially for math-heavy problems. Most
					of the work here is in C++, Python, and LaTeX, with GitHub as the place where it all stays
					searchable and easy to revisit.
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>
</BaseLayout>
